  "html": "\u003cdiv id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eIn the aftermath of World War II, Japan embraced the nuclear family as its predominant household structure, echoing anthropologist George Murdock’s assertion of its universality. However, in recent years, the prevalence of nuclear-family households has declined – a shift reflective of a desire to escape the pressures of conforming to the tightly-knit nucleus of the family unit. In response to these evolving dynamics, architects in Japan are rethinking the design of the home itself, aiming to alleviate the demands for constant cohesion within families. In Saitama, Japan, the \u003cstrong\u003eKumagaya House\u003c/strong\u003e, designed by \u003cstrong\u003e\u003ca href=\"http://choparchi.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener external noreferrer\" data-wpel-link=\"external\"\u003eCHOP+ARCHI\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e, is one such example of space redefined by this cultural shift.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560067\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560067\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7-810x648.jpg\" alt=\"Modern interior with a hallway leading to sliding glass doors, revealing an outdoor view. Light wood floors and a kitchen with a high faucet are visible on the left.\" width=\"810\" height=\"648\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7-810x648.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7-800x640.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7-768x614.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-cfsrc=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-7-810x648.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis design approach breaks up the traditional nucleus by introducing a central cruciform void that divides the home into four distinct spaces. The concept draws inspiration from the “ta-no-ji” layout, named after the Chinese character for rice field, which features a grid-like arrangement. Unlike the traditional configuration, where spaces overlap, the void acts as a buffer, creating separation between the rooms while still maintaining a subtle connection between them. Each space remains linked to the outdoors, ensuring a sense of openness and fluidity.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560063\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560063\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist kitchen with light wood flooring, a wooden island with a built-in sink, and large windows. White walls and a geometric architectural design enhance the open space.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-cfsrc=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-2-810x1215.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560075\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560075\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-810x1013.jpg\" alt=\"A modern, minimalist interior with high wood-beam ceilings, white walls, large windows, and a wooden floor. A central kitchen island is visible.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1013\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-810x1013.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-768x960.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-cfsrc=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-1-810x1013.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560065\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560065\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-810x1013.jpg\" alt=\"Interior view of a modern building with tall, white walls, large windows, and wooden accents. A narrow hallway leads to a staircase in the background.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1013\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-810x1013.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-800x1000.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-768x960.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-1229x1536.jpg 1229w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-cfsrc=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-5-810x1013.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis design approach introduces air as a key element in the home. The central void acts as a buffer, reducing tension between family members and easing the pressure to function as a single unit. By using open space instead of solid walls to divide areas, the design creates a calm and flexible environment. This allows modern families to adapt to changing needs while maintaining a sense of stability and connection, as well as respecting traditional Japanese design principles. This balance results in a living space that feels both fresh and familiar.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560066\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560066\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"A minimalist white hallway with wooden stairs and a geometric ceiling detail.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\" data-cfsrc=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-6-810x1215.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/?attachment_id=560069\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-560069\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-9-810x1215.jpg\" alt=\"Minimalist interior with wood beam ceiling, open door, large windows, and light wooden floor, creating a spacious and bright atmosphere.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-9-810x1215.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-9-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/kumagayahouse-choparchi-9